race.description: Evergreen Turf Showcase Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: THE BENTLEY (12) was below his best last start at Newcastle, but his two runs prior were genuine flashing-light efforts. He's been finding the maiden win elusive, yet he rates well in this line-up and gets another chance to finally put one away. MISS MAVERICK (10) took a big step forward last start in testing Orange conditions, chasing hard into a close second. She strips fitter and should appreciate the rise in trip. MAGIC MERLIN (1) couldn't match a smart winner at Walcha but still beat home the rest and now gains a key booking in Bullock. With race experience under his belt and natural improvement, he's in the mix despite the sticky draw. BOLD BENDER (4) finds it tough to break through, but there are efforts scattered through her form that measure up. She's worth keeping safe for the minors.
